<TITLE> BB governor tours Sidr zone to drum up farm loans Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 1 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Bank governor Salehuddin Ahmed is slated to visit cyclone-hit areas in the coming week in a bid to intensify the disbursement of farm loans, the governor's protocol officer said Saturday. Salehuddin is scheduled to visit Barisal Sunday. He is expected to meet local bankers in the two districts, the governor's protocol officer AFM Asaduzzaman told bdnews24.com. Asaduzzman said the governor had decided to visit the areas ravaged by the cyclone to remind bankers that farmers should get adequate loans quickly to cover losses caused by Sidr. He will also meet leaders of the local chambers of commerce. Bangladesh Bank executive director Khondoker Mazharul Haque will accompany the governor, he said. bdnews24.
